    • Constructor Detail

      • FastTravelHandler

        public FastTravelHandler(java.lang.String type,
                 java.lang.Object a,
                 java.lang.Object b)
        Initialise a new Fast Travel Handler. type: should be one of the following: "INIT" - asks the server for an array of strings of visited locations "SR" - indicates that the server is responding to the client outside of INIT "CR" indicates that the client is asking the server for something outside of INIT Object a: if "INIT": An array of Strings that resemble locations the player has visited. if "SR": The message the server returned to the client, if CR: the coordinate the player wants to teleport too Object b: if "INIT" || "SR": the error code (0 if no error) the server returns if CR: the location a player wants to teleport too Array v: [to be implemented] Will be an array of locations the player wants to tell the server they have found. Null otherwise
